    <etym xml:lang="ru">Сращение преверба <ref type="xr"/> (← %iam-%i) с глагольной основой
        %i*barg-%i, *barz- (и.е. %i*bherǵh-%i: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny"
                /><biblScope>146</biblScope></bibl>), являющейся общим
        скифо-славяно-балто-германским достоянием. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                    ><lang/><w>bregǫ</w><gloss><q>берегу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>берегу</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                ><lang/><w>birg-</w><gloss><q>беречь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>bergen</w><gloss><q>прятать</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. Может
        быть, сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>barəg-</w><gloss><q>принимать к
                себе</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*ambarzy(ʼmβrz-)</w><gloss><q>прием</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. также
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nyværzæn"/> ‘изголовье’, д. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_iværzun"/> ‘обещать’, и, может быть, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>.%n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref target="#ref_JRAS"
                /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр. 30</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954,
                p. 30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Fusion of the preverb <ref type="xr"/> (← %iam-%i) with the verb stem
        %i*barg-%i, *barz- (Indo-European %i*bherǵh-%i: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny"
                /><biblScope>146</biblScope></bibl>), which is a common
        Scythian-Slavic-Baltic-German heritage. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                    ><lang/><w>bregǫ</w><gloss><q>(I) take care</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>берегу</w><gloss><q>(I) take care</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>birg-</w><gloss><q>take care</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>bergen</w><gloss><q>hide
            (smth.)</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Probably, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>barəg-</w><gloss><q>take (smb.) in</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"
        ><lang/><w>*ambarzy(ʼmβrz-)</w><gloss><q>reception</q></gloss></mentioned>. See also <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_nyværzæn"/> ‘bedhead’, Digor <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_iværzun"/> ‘promise’, and, probably, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>.%n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref target="#ref_JRAS"
                /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр. 30</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954,
                p. 30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
